cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the design of a new 5G multiservice air interface to support massive Machine Type Communications (mMTC) service. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses different physical and medium access techniques to address the problem of a massive number of access attempts in mMTC. This involves the use of information theory concepts to optimize the performance of the communication system.
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the design and evaluation of a new air interface for 5G networks to support mMTC service. This falls under the domain of communications and networking.
4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper may involve the design of hardware architectures to support the new air interface for 5G networks.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may involve the use of control theory concepts to optimize the performance of the communication system.
